rComments: I loved this prof. She's very smart, nice, and explains everything with good detail. Idk if it was because the course was online but her midterms and exams were extremely easy. The assignments were harder than the test but they test your knowledge and help prepare you. I'd def recommend her.
The course was a mess, 2 profs teaching the course not the best thing ever. Exams were not even close to what you see in the lectures.

She is alright as a professor, but the issue is that she is rude and inconsiderate of her students. No replies to emails and gets angry at students for asking questions in the Zoom chat, which is pretty ridiculous. She's not a tough marker but her grading criteria is unclear and there is little room for part marks as her exams were just MC.

The tests and final were completely multiple choice. I don't know if it's because it was online or if it was always like that, but it meant that you got no part marks for process. the prof herself wasn't very engaging, and it was easy to lose focus in her lectures.

Prof Luican-Mayer always made sure her lectures prepared us well for tests, in that she did lots of examples, and went back to cover material that we were unsure about. The tests themselves weren't too hard, as they were very reflective of problems she had shown us or assigned. She also did her best to make lectures interesting with experiments.
Monotone and does not explain well.

I was so delighted to have Prof Luican-Mayer teach me Quantum Mechanics. It's such a difficult subject to teach, and she did excellently. The homework was TOUGH and very challenging, but it truly prepared us for the midterm and final, which were very fair (and she curved us!).

Professor Luican-Mayer gives great and detailed lectures to ensure that you are clear with the concept. She may be a little strict and serious in the beginning but she is really nice!!! just a gentle reminder, don't chit-chat with your friends in class and you will be fine.
Good at teaching, but very strict.

I loved Professor Luican-Mayer! She is so funny, and I loved the in-class experiments. She is very understanding and helps her students in any way possible. She does do quizzes in the lectures, so make sure you attend them. Also, the DGD's are very helpful, so go to those as well! Overall, a great prof and I would take a class with her again.

The course if-self is not difficult, however, if you need help or feedback, you are not going to get any. So lazy, not allow to look over the midterms because she will reuse them again so she won't have to work to make new tests. When you ask her questions; she refers you to TA. I find her arrogant because her lack of concerns for her students.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Dr. Luican-Mayer is one of the nicest prof's I've ever had. She makes the course simple which other prof's teaching the same course will not. Easy on the eyes too, I'd recommend the front row...

Her demos were really fun! I wish more people respected her like she deserve it. Students talked in the lectures, and with no shame would continue talking even if she stared at them. She tries to use simple English so that foreign students can understand better. Don't email her questions that can be solved any other way, talk to her, go to her offi

She makes the course easy to do well in. If you did well in physics in high school you'll probably be fine for her course. Pop quizzes are nothing to be scared of, literally one formula to use. Midterms aren't too bad, second one was a bit harder but still fair. Exam was easy. Plus she's gorgeous
This professor is nice, midterm&exam are pretty straight-forward question, practice a few then you wont get low marks

Horrific Prof, just copies equations from the textbook onto the board. If a student asks a question, she does not know how to answer it because she does not know the material herself, she tells you to ask your DGD leader

I failed her class last year because I never attended lectures but I took it again because shes easy on the eyes. She changed her style from ppt lectures to writing on chalkboard which slowed down the tempo for the better, however, I feel like too much time is dedicated to derivations. I recommend doing the Mastering Physics Modules to fill in gaps

Dr. Luican-Mayer is a pretty decent prof. She can deliver the material adequately. Her ppt slides are clear and concise although she forgot to post lectures or posted them a bit late. Its her first time teaching so it is understandable. Overall, if you do the work (Assignments + DGDs), you'll get the grade.   P.S:  She's hot. Don't skip class.

She's my favourite prof this semester! She may be inexperienced, but she was very organized considering she had to write all her slides and tests. She is also the most approachable prof I've ever had. I would get there early for class and she would always initiate conversation with her students about pretty much anything. I also loved the bonuses!

New, inexperienced, disorganized. BUT, before you pass judgement, she is still MILES better than Stadnik. Since this is her 1st time teaching, there's greater chances that she'll improve. The tests/exams are SUPER long and if you hate mornings know her quizzes are at 830am sharp. Where she does best is 1-on-1... GO TO HER OFFICE HOURS.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: She's very new and it shows in her teaching style. She's way better than Stadnik though, so pick her over him if you have the choice. The course is hard and she's a super weird grader which isnt great but she is trying and she will only get better with time.

-She goes through topics either too slow or too fast  -The projector screen had a blue dim which made it nearly impossible to read the txt. book problems -Often late to upload lecture notes -Writes on chalkboard too small -Writes on digital pad too sloppy (not entirely her fault) -Dgd prof was hard to understand (language barrier)
It's never her fault, always the students' fault. Gives large assignments without warning, regardless of midterms or work in other classes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: She's not that good. Doesn't listen to student feedback, blames the students for problems with the course.
GOOD PROF
